\section{Invariant columns}{


Every \code{mdl_tbl} carries these columns; they may be reordered by row but not
removed or renamed. Dropping any of them (e.g. through \code{\link[dplyr:select]{dplyr::select()}})
returns a plain \code{data.frame} with a message.
\itemize{
\item \code{id} — hash identifying the model (links rows to the formula matrix)
\item \code{formula_index} — the model's row of the formula matrix
\item \code{data_id} — name of the dataset the model was fit on
\item \code{name} — the label the object was given when added to the table
\item \code{model_call} — the fitting function (e.g. \code{lm}, \code{coxph}); \code{NA} until fit
\item \code{formula_call} — the model formula as text
\item \code{number} — number of right-hand-side terms (the "adjustment degree")
\item \code{outcome}, \code{exposure}, \code{mediator}, \code{interaction} — terms by causal role
\item \code{strata}, \code{level} — the stratifying term and this model's stratum
\item \code{subset} — the \code{\link[=subset_data]{subset_data()}} instruction the model was fit under
\item \code{model_parameters} — parameter-level estimates (a list of data frames)
\item \code{model_summary} — model-level statistics (a list)
\item \code{fit_status} — \code{TRUE} if the model fit; \code{FALSE} if it failed or has not
been fit yet
}
}

\section{Combining tables}{


Model tables combine through \code{model_table(x, y)} (or \code{vctrs::vec_rbind()});
formula matrices, term tables, and data lists are merged and deduplicated,
with the first (left-most) definition of a term kept. \code{\link[dplyr:bind_rows]{dplyr::bind_rows()}}
only works when the rows already belong to the first table (it strips
attributes before they can be reconciled); combining unrelated tables with
it returns a plain \code{data.frame} with a message pointing back to
\code{model_table()}.
}

